#Approach:

Find How Many Times Array is Rotated – Binary Search Approach

Sorted rotated array me jitni baar array rotate hota hai,
utni hi position par minimum element aa jata hai.
Isliye problem ko directly minimum element ka index find karne me convert kar sakte hain.

Agar minimum element index i par hai,
to array i times rotated hai.

Approach:
Hum binary search use karte hain.

Har step par check karte hain ki kaunsa half sorted hai.

Agar left half sorted hai:
to us half ka minimum nums[low] hoga.
Isliye nums[low] ko possible answer maan kar
right side me search karte hain, kyunki actual minimum dusre half me ho sakta hai.

Agar left half sorted nahi hai:
to iska matlab rotation point left half me hai
aur nums[mid] possible minimum ho sakta hai.
Isliye nums[mid] ko answer ke liye consider karte hain
aur left side me search karte hain.

Poore process me hum minimum element aur uska index track karte rehte hain.

End me minimum element ka index hi total rotations hota hai.

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

Number of rotations = index of minimum element


#Code:

class Solution {
    public int findKRotation(int[] nums) {
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;
        int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        int index = -1;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            // if left half is sorted
            if(nums[low] <= nums[mid]){
                if(nums[low] < ans){
                    ans = nums[low];
                    index = low;
                }
                low = mid + 1;
            }
            // right half is sorted, minimum lies in left half including mid
            else{
                if(nums[mid] < ans){
                    ans = nums[mid];
                    index = mid;
                }
                high = mid - 1;
            }
        }
        return index;
    }
}
